cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a new information theoretic framework for quantifying data uncertainty and applies it to predictive uncertainty quantification of neural network models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the framework leverages a quantum physical description of the metric space, which suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The application of the framework to predictive uncertainty quantification of neural network models suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also presents experimental comparisons with established uncertainty quantification methods, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper specifically focuses on non-parametric and non-intrusive surrogate tools for uncertainty quantification, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
